1
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,260
Look at these exam papers.

2
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:28,680
Even the mistakes are exactly the same.

3
00:00:28,840 --> 00:00:30,120
If a student hadn't reminded me,

4
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:32,119
they would have gotten away with it.

5
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:33,920
Wang Yu,

6
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:35,520
help me find out

7
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,760
who leaked the answers.

8
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:40,960
Okay, I'll get right on it.

9
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:45,640
So the streaming platform is settled.

10
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:48,280
Are you handling control, operations, and directing all by yourself?

11
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:50,280
Is there anyone else?

12
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:51,600
Not really.

13
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,680
It's just that you don't want a salary

14
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:54,940
or a cut of the profits.

15
00:00:55,160 --> 00:00:58,020
I just need you to reach 300,000 as soon as possible.

16
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:00,160
But 300,000 isn't that easy to earn.

17
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:01,560
What?

18
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:03,520
You want to back out?

19
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:04,879
Of course not.

20
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:07,280
It's just that everything is hard at the beginning.

21
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:09,680
I'm afraid you won't be able to stick it out.

22
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:11,560
You should worry about yourself.

23
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:31,200
Can't we just use products to attract traffic?

24
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:32,400
No.

25
00:01:32,479 --> 00:01:34,759
Streamers who sell directly have a fan base.

26
00:01:34,759 --> 00:01:35,479
Yeah.

27
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:38,280
This is a list I made.

28
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:40,160
Once we start the live stream,

29
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,560
we can't just interrupt it.

30
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,120
I need to look for a venue for the live stream.

31
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,759
Are you okay going to the company alone?

32
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:45,360
Yes.

33
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:50,280
What do you mean by finding a subordinate contact?

34
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,720
Uncle He will help you connect with the boss.

35
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:54,080
The first visit to the company will go smoothly,

36
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:56,000
but it'll be hard to maintain if the boss is too busy later on.

37
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,120
You need to find a subordinate contact in the company

38
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:00,250
to handle future internal handovers.

39
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:10,090
All that's missing is a subordinate contact.

40
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,320
I have no idea at all.

41
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,760
With Yang Xiu helping to connect,

42
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:25,760
the follow-up with the enterprise won't be a problem.

43
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:27,400
Yang Qian.

44
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:30,320
Have you heard of White Swan Clothing near the school?

45
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,250
I've heard of it.

46
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:34,079
Then do you know someone named Yang Xiu?

47
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,400
Very well.

48
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,720
Are you Yin Zixi?

49
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:45,400
Yes.

50
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,480
Oh my.

51
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:49,160
I didn't even know Qianqian had a classmate who knows our boss.

52
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:50,840
Auntie, is your surname also Yang?

53
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:51,680
Yes.

54
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,160
Our whole family's surname is Yang.

55
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,120
Three Yangs bring good fortune.

56
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,640
Yang, Yang, Yang.

57
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:56,800
Come on, let's go inside.

58
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:57,760
Okay.

59
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,360
Kai.

60
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,680
The East Building Music Club should be abandoned, right?

61
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,280
They have all moved to the new building.

62
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,680
Could you help me rent it?

63
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,700
It's not for me.

64
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:18,329
Yin Zixi, Class One, Journalism Department.

65
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,320
Oh.

66
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,200
She was elected as this year's student representative.

67
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,600
Then there's no problem.

68
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:23,360
Thanks for your help.

69
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,520
Yeah, okay.

70
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,280
Just go to the front desk and sign.

71
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,000
Okay.

72
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:48,400
Hello, I'm here to sign the bill.

73
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,000
Hey, who is that?

74
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,400
She is carrying so many samples.

75
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:55,640
She's my daughter's classmate and also the boss's friend.

76
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:56,760
The boss's friend?

77
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,730
Since when does the boss have such a young friend?

78
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,320
Hello.

79
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:08,840
Hello.

80
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,600
Is this An Yufan from Xihai University?

81
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:11,040
Yes.

82
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,760
I need to set up a dedicated broadband line here.

83
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:13,240
Okay.

84
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,490
I'll be right there.

85
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:33,440
Why are there so few cars?

86
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:38,880
Miss.

87
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,760
Have you picked up your goods?

88
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:41,080
Yes.

89
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,680
I heard

90
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,570
you're a friend of the boss.

91
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,250
Introduced by a friend.

92
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:50,159
It must be tiring to carry so many goods.

93
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,000
How are you getting back?

94
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:52,880
Do you need my help?

95
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:53,680
No, thanks.

96
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:56,920
These samples

97
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,360
are quite expensive.

98
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,440
If they get damaged on the way,

99
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:01,700
that wouldn't be good.

100
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,760
Why don't you take my car?

101
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,380
I'll take you back.

102
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,320
Zixi,

103
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,040
you dropped your jacket.

104
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,240
You must be from White Swan Apparel.

105
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,360
Who are you?

106
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:20,080
These bags of clothes,

107
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,810
just help me put them in the car.

108
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,160
Humph.

109
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,560
Why should I carry them for you?

110
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,080
Or do you want me to find your boss

111
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:27,840
and tell him

112
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:30,120
how you treat his guests?

113
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:34,120
Hey.

114
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:35,520
Fine, I'll take them.

115
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:54,600
What a cool car.

116
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,000
Where did this come from?

117
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,520
It belongs to Uncle He.

118
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,120
I knew he was no ordinary man.

119
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,400
Good thing you came in time just now.

120
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:07,300
By the way, weren't you setting up the livestream room?

121
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,120
What's wrong with you?

122
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,650
I haven't driven in a long time.

123
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:17,960
This car accelerates a bit fast.

124
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,440
Ah, we're finally here.

125
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,400
I thought I was going to die.

126
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,320
Did you set all this up?

127
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:36,960
I did some decorating.

128
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:40,120
The computer and streaming equipment are also set up.

129
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,320
What about these?

130
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,480
These were left by the music club.

131
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,560
I cleaned them up a bit.

132
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,600
We can use them as decorations.

133
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,400
Oh.

134
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,520
Hello, fans.

135
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:10,360
Good morning.

136
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:12,180
Did you sleep well last night?

137
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:12,920
By the way,

138
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,560
I heard some huge gossip today.

139
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,360
It's about...

140
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:17,620
Everything is ready for the live stream.

141
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,320
At first, we need to get as much platform traffic as possible.

142
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:22,320
First, we need perfect attendance.

143
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,120
It's best to win the duration award.

144
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,050
Duration award?

145
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,640
A total of 60 hours over 10 consecutive days.

146
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:28,640
That's an average of six hours a day.

147
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,120
Considering unexpected events and school activities,

148
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,980
we need at least eight hours a day.

149
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:33,760
Right.

150
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:41,000
Ten hours of class,

151
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,080
two hours for meals,

152
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:42,840
and eight hours of sleep a day.

153
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,720
Stop calculating.

154
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,960
There's not enough time.

155
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:47,090
Then how can we win the duration award?

156
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,600
Deducting class time...

157
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,760
Deducting meal time...

158
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,159
Deducting sleep time...

159
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,090
This is the only way.

160
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,159
Guarantee ten consecutive days.

161
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:56,760
We'll broadcast as much as we can.

162
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:57,840
Are you a devil?

163
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,080
How is it?

164
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:08,720
Is it okay?

165
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,280
It's fine.

166
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,620
Come and enter the live stream ID.

167
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,600
Casting Director Xi Chongjing

168
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,520
Props Assistant Li Kunxiao

169
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:49,480
Production Vehicle Yi Mingle

170
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:51,440
Yitong
